pass100 golden — fj-lax: TopK complement-key radix for F32/F16/BF16/U32/U64/I32 (O(n log n) -> O(n))
target=eval/topk_64k_k128_f32 (eval_top_k Literal-backed numeric path)
lever=ALGORITHM REPLACEMENT (different complexity class). eval_top_k_dense covered only i64/f64 dense storage; F32/F16/BF16/U32/U64/I32 (Literal-backed) fell to the generic O(n log n) full comparison sort then take-k. Added a Literal-backed branch mirroring the sort path (pass99): per-dtype-family complement key (!f64_total_order_key(as_f64) for floats, !as_u64 for unsigned, !((as_i64 as u64)^(1<<63)) for signed), then order_top_k_pairs — which for small k uses O(n) partial selection (select_nth_unstable) and for large k a stable LSD radix.
method=same-bench A/B on RCH Criterion; baseline = git-stashed eval_top_k (generic comparison-sort top-k for F32); normalized by eval/sort_calib_reduce_64k_i64 (ReduceSum, UNAFFECTED) calibration.
calibration_reduce=candidate 10.665us vs baseline 9.0399us -> candidate worker 1.18x slower
topk_64k_k128_f32=baseline 9.7631ms [9.171, 10.366] vs candidate 702.43us [689.79, 716.56] = 13.9x raw -> 16.4x worker-corrected
score=impact 5 (top_k is common in ML: sampling, beam search, retrieval; large absolute win) x confidence 5 (BIT-EXACT vs generic; parity test k=1/32/257 + 6 topk tests pass) / effort 2 = 12.5
alien_primitive=partial selection (select_nth_unstable, O(n)) + complement-key LSD radix instead of a full comparison sort. 100% safe Rust.
isomorphism=BIT-IDENTICAL to the generic top_k for each dtype family. The complement key turns ascending into descending-by-value, and order_top_k_pairs keeps equal values in ascending in-slice-index tie order — exactly the generic comparator compare_sort_keys(b,a).then(a_idx.cmp(b_idx)). Float keys reproduce SortKey::Float(as_f64).total_cmp; Unsigned reproduce Unsigned cmp; Signed reproduce signed cmp. Values output = the original literals (exact bits); indices = i64 in-slice indices. F64/I64 handled by the dense branches above; Bool/Complex fall through to generic.
golden_note=top_k_f32_radix_matches_reference: F32 top_k values+indices for k in {1,32,257} (covering partial-select and radix paths) vs an independent descending-total_cmp / ascending-index reference over NaN/+-inf/+-0/payload/dups, compared by bits. 6 topk tests pass.
validation=RCH cargo test -p fj-lax --release top_k: 6 passed; RCH cargo clippy -p fj-lax --release --all-targets --no-deps -- -D warnings: clean.
note=one branch covers all of F32/F16/BF16/U32/U64/I32 (mirrors the pass99 sort generalization); only F32 is benched/parity-tested directly, the others share the identical key-derivation + ordering machinery (U32 key validated by pass99's sort u32 test).
